FeedPackage.Description: NConf is an advanced configuration system for .Net projects. It's written out of the need for more advanced configuration than what .Net provides. The key features it supports is multiple configuration sources, simple to use syntax, the ability to reload/update configuration at runtime, and the easy ability to implement custom configuration sources.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: This is the initial release. It includes a complete working configuration system, and working dictionary, SQL and app.config sources. All classes should also be threadsafe.

FeedPackage.Description: NConf is an advanced configuration system for .Net projects. It's written out of the need for more advanced configuration than what .Net provides. The key features it supports is multiple configuration sources, simple to use syntax, the ability to reload/update configuration at runtime, and the easy ability to implement custom configuration sources.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: This is the initial release. It includes a complete working configuration system, and working dictionary, SQL and app.config sources. All classes should also be threadsafe.

FeedPackage.Description:
NContext is an extensible, composable Domain-Driven-Design application framework for .NET 4.0.
This project is a culmination and on-going effort of research done over the course of two years studying the subject. It borrows many patterns, implementations, concepts from a variety of software architects in the field. That said ... NContext is unique and innovative in how it allows you to design your application without tying it down to any specific technology or pattern. It also introduces new concepts in designing your domain(s). It has few dependencies and is broken into additional addon modules for things like: Entity Framework, Enterprise Library, WCF, and is dependency-injection container agnostic. Unity support has been added with the intentions of supporting all popular containers in the near future.
FeedPackage.Summary: NContext is an extensible, composable domain-driven-design application framework for .NET 4.0.
FeedPackage.Title: NContext
